article.headline: Drexel 56, Vermont 42
article.story: PHILADELPHIA (AP) -- Kenell Sanchez scored a game-high 17 points and Bashir Mason had 15 to lead Drexel to a 56-42 win over Vermont on Saturday. The Dragons (14-14) led by as many as 15 and never trailed in the second half in gaining their second win in the last eight games. Vermont (11-13) fell to 3-10 in road games this season. Mason, who scored 11 of his points in the second half, hit a hook shot with 15:45 remaining in the game to cap a 12-2 run and give the Dragons a 37-23 lead. He added a 3-pointer 1:33 later to give the Dragons their biggest lead, 40-25. Drexel led by double digits throughout most of the second half, but with 3:23 remaining Vermont's Ryan Schneider hit a pair of free throws to cut the margin to 49-40. Chaz Crawford added 10 points, 12 rebounds and a game-high seven blocks for the Dragons. Frank Elegar also pulled down 12 rebounds for Drexel. Vermont shot 27 percent from the field, making only 16-of-60 field goal attempts. Mike Trimboli led the Catamounts with 11 points. Chris Holm grabbed a team-high 11 rebounds for Vermont. The lead changed hands six times in the first half before Mason hit a jump shot as time expired to give Drexel a 29-21 halftime edge. Sanchez scored on a layup with 8:26 remaining in the first half to give the Dragons a 14-12 lead, and Drexel never trailed after that.
